{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771337147,"nonce":"fyTEqkvzRPNc7D9NHFHe8k3nQUQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rnRdC","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/217","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_create.sh --draft-pr uses wrong repo, title, and identity for project-repo PRs","message":"## Bug\n\nWhen `worktree_create.sh --draft-pr` creates a draft PR for a **project repo** (e.g. `unh_marine_autonomy`), the PR metadata is incorrect in multiple ways:\n\n### 1. Wrong issue link\nThe PR body references the **workspace repo's** issue number (`ros2_agent_workspace/issues/N`) instead of the project repo's issue (`unh_marine_autonomy/issues/N`). Since the issue lives in the project repo, the link points to a non-existent or unrelated workspace issue.\n\n### 2. Wrong PR title\nThe PR title doesn't reflect the actual issue. In the observed case, the title was `WIP: Add ephemeral git identity for host-based agents in shared workspaces` for a PR about adding `manda_coverage` to `core.repos`. The title appears to come from a stale value or template rather than the actual issue being worked on.\n\n### 3. Wrong AI identity\nThe PR signature uses generic `AI Agent` / `Unknown` instead of the session's `$AGENT_NAME` / `$AGENT_MODEL` environment variables.\n\n### Observed example\n\n**PR**: https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/64\n**Issue**: https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/issues/63\n\nDraft PR was created with:\n```\nTitle: WIP: Add ephemeral git identity for host-based agents in shared workspaces\nBody:  ...tracks ongoing work for https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/63\nSig:   AI Agent / Unknown\n```\n\nShould have been:\n```\nTitle: WIP: Add manda_coverage to core.repos\nBody:  ...tracks ongoing work for https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/issues/63\nSig:   Claude Code Agent / Claude Opus 4.6\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen `--draft-pr` targets a project repo, the script should:\n- Fetch the issue title and URL from the **project repo** (using `--repo-slug` or auto-detected repo)\n- Use `$AGENT_NAME` / `$AGENT_MODEL` for the signature (falling back to generic only if unset)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}